This recording is an amplified version of a previously uploaded call (XC606119). I hope that it makes assessing its credentials easier for either Eastern or Western Yellow Wagtail.

This recording features calls from one (of two) Yellow Wagtails that were present for several days in a rank grassy field containing cattle. Often the birds were elsewhere and sometimes just one was present. In terms of appearance, the two were similar. Sometimes they kept company, sometimes not. Because the birds' upperparts were greyish with a veneer of brown (although their undertail coverts were pale yellow), some observers identified them as Eastern Yellow Wagtail (Motacilla tschutensis). I have to say that I am not in favour, taxonomically, of the Yellow Wagtail group being split into Eastern and Western 'species'. However, put those views to one side. Being an Irish birdwatcher, I don't have much experience of 'flava wagtail' calls - so I would be most grateful if others might have an opinion about the calls' best fit to species/subspecies.
